            "Certificate of Undergraduate Study in Sports, Society & Civic Leadership The Certificate of Undergraduate Study (CUGS) in Sports, Society, & Civic Leadership provides a sequence of courses that combines humanities topics (such history, anthropology, and english) with sports communications and journalism (such as public relations and communications) equipping students with well-rounded approach to careers in the sports industry, non-profits, community organizations and to understand how sports operates in historical and social spheres."
